.\" Man page for tk, the Ticket CLI.
.\" View with: man -l man/tk.1
.TH TK 1 "May 2026" "" "Ticket Manual"
.SH NAME
tk \- agent-first Ticket Project command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tk
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.br
.B tk
\fIcommand\fR
[\fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tk
is the command-line executable for
.B Ticket Project,
an agent-first tool for managing backend-agnostic work items through a
local-first Repository Store and explicit backend Promotion.
.PP
This manual documents the command surface available in the current binary.
Future v1 commands are intentionally omitted until they are implemented.
.PP
New
.B Tickets
are local by default. A configured Remote does not make new Tickets
backend-backed; Promotion is the explicit boundary where local state becomes
backend intent.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print top-level help.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the current version.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Repository setup
.TP
.B tk init
Initialize the Repository Store for the current git repository.
.PP
The Repository Store is a SQLite database at
\fI<git-common-dir>/tk/ticket.db\fR. It is shared by all git worktrees for the
same repository and is untracked local state.
.PP
.B tk init
is idempotent. If the store already exists and is current, it reports the
existing path instead of recreating it.
.SS Creating Tickets
.TP
\fBtk add\fR \fB\-F\fR \fIfile\fR
.TQ
\fBtk add\fR \fB\-F\fR \fB\-\fR
.TQ
\fBtk add\fR \fB\-\-file\fR \fIfile\fR
.TQ
\fBtk add\fR \fB\-\-file\fR=\fIfile\fR
.TQ
\fBtk add\fR \fB\-\-file\fR \fB\-\fR
Create a local task Ticket from git-commit-style message input.
.PP
.B \-F
and
.B \-\-file
read the message from a file. Use
.B \-
to read the message from standard input. Exactly one
.B \-F
or
.B \-\-file
flag is required in the current binary.
.PP
The first paragraph becomes the Ticket title. Later paragraphs become the
body. An empty message aborts creation. The created Ticket has Priority
.B P2
and Item Status
.BR open .
.PP
On success,
.B tk add
prints:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
Created Ticket: <display-id> - <title>
Priority: P2
Status: open
.fi
.RE
.PP
The current binary does not implement
.BR \-\-bug ,
.BR \-\-epic ,
.BR \-\-priority ,
.BR \-\-parent ,
repeatable
.BR \-m ,
or editor mode.
.SS Reading the List Tree
.TP
\fBtk list\fR [\fB\-\-all\fR | \fB\-\-ready\fR | \fB\-\-blocked\fR | \fB\-\-active\fR] [\fB\-\-local\fR | \fB\-\-remote\fR]
Render the Repository Store List Tree.
.PP
The default view shows open and active Tickets and Epics. Epics render as
top-level rows, child Tickets render under their Epic with tree glyphs, and
unparented Tickets render as top-level rows.
.PP
.B \-\-all
includes done items.
.B \-\-ready
shows open Tickets with no unresolved Dependencies or External Blockers.
.B \-\-blocked
shows open or active Tickets with unresolved Dependencies or External Blockers.
.B \-\-active
shows active Tickets and Epics, retaining inactive Epics as containers for
active child Tickets.
.PP
.B \-\-local
shows only local items.
.B \-\-remote
shows only Backend-backed items. The current binary can read backend-origin
rows seeded by tests or future sync paths, but it does not promote or pull
backend items yet.
.PP
On success with one local Ticket,
.B tk list
prints:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
○ project-1 ● P2 Investigate flaky login retry
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Total: 1 item (1 open)

Status: ○ open  ◐ active  ✓ done
.fi
.RE
.SS Selecting Ready Work
.TP
\fBtk next\fR [\fB\-\-all\fR]
Select the next ready Ticket.
.PP
.B tk next
selects open Tickets with no unresolved Dependencies or External Blockers. It
orders ready Tickets by local Priority, then creation order, and never selects
Epics.
.PP
When Workspace Scope support lands,
.B tk next
will default to the active Workspace Scope and
.B \-\-all
will ignore that scope. In the current binary, Workspace Scope discovery has
not landed yet, so
.B tk next
searches all ready Tickets.
.PP
On success,
.B tk next
prints:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
<display-id> <priority> <title>
.fi
.RE
.PP
If no ready Ticket matches,
.B tk next
returns exit status 1 and writes
.B tk next: no ready Tickets
to standard error.
.SS Agent briefing
.TP
.B tk prime
Print static agent workflow guidance to standard output.
.PP
.B tk prime
does not require an initialized Repository Store and writes nothing to
standard error on success.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Logical failure, such as missing Repository Store or invalid message input.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.TP
.B 3
Unexpected internal error.
.SH EXAMPLES
Initialize a repository-local store:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk init
.fi
.RE
.PP
Create a local Ticket from a file:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk add -F followup.md
.fi
.RE
.PP
Create a local Ticket from standard input:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk add -F - <<'EOF'
Investigate flaky login retry

Repro is intermittent on the staging cluster.
First seen 2026-04-30.
EOF
.fi
.RE
.PP
List visible work:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk list
tk list --ready
.fi
.RE
.PP
Select the next ready Ticket:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk next
.fi
.RE
.PP
Print agent guidance:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
tk prime
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
The project README, CONTEXT.md domain glossary, docs/cli.md v1 target
surface, and ADRs under docs/adr/.
